<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p>Public Transport</p><br/><p>Accrington Victoria Community Hospital is well served by public transport links. Please visit the <a href="http://www.traveline-northwest.co.uk/" target="_blank">Traveline Website</a> for public transport information and to plan your journey. </p><br/><p>By Bus</p><br/><p>For the latest bus timetable please <a href="http://www.traveline-northwest.co.uk/" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p><br/><p><strong>Parking</strong></p><br/><p>All visitors, patient and staff are required to pay and display a ticket when using a designated car parking space at the hospital.</p><br/><p> </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>Parking<br/>All visitors, patient and staff are required to pay and display a ticket when using a designated car parking space at the hospital.<br/><br/>Charges<br/>0-3 hours = £1.90p<br/><br/>3-8 hours = £2.80p<br/><br/>8-24 hours = £3.50p<br/><br/>Access to the car park is made via Garden Street.<br/><br/>The Trust Board have made the decision to charge blue badge holders for parking to show equity across all staff, patients and visitor groups. This decision was implemented in May 2018 and the standard tariff charges now apply to all across the East Lancashire Hospital sites. The Trust has made sure blue badge parking continues to be accessible and convenient for the use of its facilities.</p>
